        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1805111" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16651457867186926543">this book practically changed my life. utter genius. i think feuerbach is one of the most overlooked philosophers ever. his writing is lucid and easy to follow, it&apos;s logical and convincing, and he doesn&apos;t pander to his audience. he also doesn&apos;t say that people who believe in christianity are stupid - rather, he points out why it would be logical to believe in a god, but also why it is more logical that christianity is a falsity. <br/><br/>i try to make everyone i know who i interested in religion read it,</span>
  <span id="freeText16651457867186926543" style="display:none">this book practically changed my life. utter genius. i think feuerbach is one of the most overlooked philosophers ever. his writing is lucid and easy to follow, it's logical and convincing, and he doesn't pander to his audience. he also doesn't say that people who believe in christianity are stupid - rather, he points out why it would be logical to believe in a god, but also why it is more logical that christianity is a falsity. <br /><br />i try to make everyone i know who i interested in religion read it, which means i should read it again. interestingly, i went to use it for a paper while at columbia, and i had to inter-library loan it - this from the 6th largest collection in the country. (so thank you, brown, for keeping religious dissedents around!)</span>
