  <span id="freeText4952204684558793875" style="display:none">Sadly, this book does not have much to offer to the modern man whose ears are constantly bombarded with atheism; but in this short book Feuerbach laid the foundations for modern atheism, a foundation later cultivated by Karl Marx. In the process, Feuerbach was dwarfed by the colossal stature of Marx and Hegel and somewhat forgotten.<br /><br />I can't say this book has much to offer for someone who has read and understood Hegel, but for a lamen (Like yours truly) it's a pleasant simplification.<br /><br /></span>
