        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1217237840" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14590039462232257712">As one of the prime proponents of the German rationalism that undermined Christianity in England and America, resulting in fundamentalism on the one hand and a sort of atheistic liberalism on the other, this enemy of Christianity proposes some interesting criticisms of the religion as practiced. The idea that the God most people worship is merely a reflection of themselves, at least of their own ideals, or their own beliefs, is certainly true. While many of his conclusions are ludicrous he does </span>
  <span id="freeText14590039462232257712" style="display:none">As one of the prime proponents of the German rationalism that undermined Christianity in England and America, resulting in fundamentalism on the one hand and a sort of atheistic liberalism on the other, this enemy of Christianity proposes some interesting criticisms of the religion as practiced. The idea that the God most people worship is merely a reflection of themselves, at least of their own ideals, or their own beliefs, is certainly true. While many of his conclusions are ludicrous he does make good points that should make any Bible-believer examine why he believes what he believes and how that belief is based on the Bible or his own prejudices, bigotry, fear, paranoia, and self-righteousness.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14590039462232257712" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
